    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A range of purplish red or pink colors resembling the color of reddish lake pigments, which are organic pigments prepared by precipitation of a dye on a powdered, inorganic substrate. The color term "lake" refers particularly to the colors of cochineal, kermes, madder, lac, etc., which are all reddish in color and used in oil painting.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000009521/Color: Universal Language and Dictionary (1976)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049919/American Heritage College Dictionary (1997)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指一特定範圍的紫紅色或粉紅色色彩，近似於紅色的色澱顏料。色澱為有機顏料，由粉末狀無機基質染料之沉澱物所製成。「色澱紅」這個詞彙尤指用於油畫的胭脂紅色、蟲胭脂色、茜草色、蟲膠色等紅色顏料之顏色。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een reeks paarsachtig rode of roze kleuren die lijken op de kleur van karmijnroodachtige pigmenten, organische pigmenten die worden gemaakt door het laten bezinken van een verfstof in een anorganisch substraat in poedervorm. De kleurenterm 'karmijn' verwijst met name naar de kleuren van cochenille, kermes, meekraprood, lak, etc., allen roodachtig van kleur en gebruikt bij schilderen met olieverf.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Uma gama de cores vermelho-púrpura ou rosa que lembram a cor dos pigmentos de laca avermelhada, que são pigmentos orgânicos preparados pela precipitação de um corante em um substrato inorgânico em pó. O termo de cor "lago" se refere particularmente às cores de cochonilha, kermes, garança, laca, etc., que são todas de cor avermelhada e usadas em pintura a óleo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
